The paper deals with the design of a secure and trustworthy spectrum access system (SAS) for the 3.5 GHz CBRS band, which involves the use of cryptographic techniques and blockchain technology. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
